 [ ] Define AgentMetadata class extending BaseModel\n- [ ] Define agent_name field with required validation\n- [ ] Define description field as Optional[str]\n- [ ] Define language field with default \"python\"\n- [ ] Define entrypoint field with required validation\n- [ ] Define port field with default 8080 and range validation\n- [ ] Define build_mode field with default \"local\"\n- [ ] Define region field as Optional[str]\n- [ ] Define version field as Optional[str]\n- [ ] Define requirements_file field as Optional[str]\n- [ ] Add validator for language field (must be \"python\" or \"java\")\n- [ ] Add validator for build_mode field (must be \"local\" or \"cloud\")\n- [ ] Add validator for port field (must be 1-65535)\n- [ ] Add comprehensive docstrings\n\n**Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.models.metadata import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='test'); print(m)\"` and verify it validates correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Implement agentcube/services/__init__.py - Service initialization\n- [ ] Export MetadataService class\n- [ ] Add package-level docstring\n- [ ] Configure logging for services module\n\n**Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService; print(MetadataService)\"` and verify it imports correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Implement agentcube/services/metadata_service.py - MetadataService class structure\n- [ ] Import Path from pathlib\n- [ ] Import yaml\n- [ ] Import AgentMetadata from models\n- [ ] Import logging\n- [ ] Define MetadataService class\n- [ ] Implement __init__ method with verbose parameter\n- [ ] Initialize logger with level based on verbose\n- [ ] Add class docstring\n\n**Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService; s = MetadataService(); print(s)\"` and verify it instantiates\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Implement MetadataService.load_metadata method\n- [ ] Define load_metadata method with workspace_path parameter\n- [ ] Implement fallback logic for metadata files (agent_metadata.yaml, agent.yaml, metadata.yaml)\n- [ ] For each filename, check if file exists\n- [ ] If file exists, load and parse YAML\n- [ ] Create and return AgentMetadata instance from parsed data\n- [ ] Handle YAML parsing errors\n- [ ] Raise FileNotFoundError if no metadata file found\n- [ ] Add error logging\n\n**Verification**: Create test metadata file and run `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService; s = MetadataService(); m = s.load_metadata(Path('test')); print(m.agent_name)\"` and verify it loads\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Implement MetadataService.save_metadata method\n- [ ] Define save_metadata method with workspace_path and metadata parameters\n- [ ] Construct metadata_path as workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n- [ ] Open metadata_path for writing\n- [ ] Use yaml.dump to write metadata\n- [ ] Exclude None fields using model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n- [ ] Set default_flow_style=False for readability\n- [ ] Set indent=2 for formatting\n- [ ] Set sort_keys=False to preserve field order\n- [ ] Handle file write errors\n- [ ] Add success logging\n\n**Verification**: Create metadata instance, save it, and verify file exists with correct content\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Implement MetadataService.validate_workspace method\n- [ ] Define validate_workspace method with workspace_path parameter\n- [ ] Load metadata from workspace\n- [ ] Check metadata.language field\n- [ ] If python, call _validate_python_workspace\n- [ ] If java, call _validate_java_workspace\n- [ ] Return True if validation passes\n- [ ] Add error handling for unknown languages\n\n**Verification**: Create test workspace with valid metadata and run validation\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Implement MetadataService._validate_python_workspace method\n- [ ] Define _validate_python_workspace method with workspace_path and metadata parameters\n- [ ] Use glob to find all *.py files in workspace\n- [ ] Convert glob result