mmand implementation\n7. **Comprehensive test suites** - Unit, integration, and E2E tests\n8. **Documentation** - README and usage examples\n9. **Example workspaces** - Python and Java examples\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All Python files compile without errors\n- All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n- All integration tests pass\n- All E2E tests pass\n- `agentcube pack --help` displays comprehensive help\n- `agentcube pack` works on Python workspaces\n- `agentcube pack` works on Java workspaces\n- CLI option overrides work correctly\n- Dockerfiles are generated correctly for both languages\n- Metadata files are created and updated correctly\n- Error handling is comprehensive with clear messages\n- Verbose mode provides detailed logging\n- Code passes static analysis (flake8, mypy, black)\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n- Examples work correctly\n\n### Dependencies\n- Python 3.10+\n- typer[all] >=0.9.0\n- pydantic >=2.0.0\n- pyyaml >=6.0\n- docker >=6.0.0\n- rich >=13.0.0\n- packaging >=23.0\n- pytest (for testing)\n- flake8 (for linting)\n- mypy (for type checking)\n- black (for formatting)\n\n### Blocked By\n- None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n\n### Blocks\n- AR-021: CLI build command (depends on pack command output)\n- AR-022: CLI publish command (depends on pack and build commands)\n- AR-023: CLI invoke command (depends on publish command)\n- AR-024: CLI status command (depends on publish command)\n\n### Notes\n- Pack command is the foundation for all other CLI commands\n- Supports Python and Java workspaces initially\n- Uses intelligent inference for defaults to minimize configuration\n- Generates optimized Dockerfiles following best practices\n- Comprehensive error handling with clear user feedback\n- Rich progress display for better user experience\n- Extensive test coverage ensures reliability\n- Examples provided for quick start","additions":993,"deletions":10},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-g